Description: The Adult Social Care Outcomes Framework (ASCOF) measures how well care and support services achieve the outcomes that matter most to people. The ASCOF is used both locally and nationally to set priorities for care and support, measure progress and strengthen transparency and accountability.
Name: Measures from the Adult Social Care Outcomes Framework, England
Notes: The report is an interactive Power BI and the raw data is available in an Open data CSV
Sizing Notes: Although this initially appears to be complex a CSV file is available, however some work may be required to determine what the dimensions should be named.
